Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Arrange graham squares in single layer in 15x10x1-inch baking pan. Place butter and sugar in medium saucepan. Bring to boil on medium heat; boil 2 minutes. Pour over grahams; immediately spread to completely cover all grahams. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly. Sprinkle with chocolate chunks. Bake an additional 1 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is melted. Remove from oven; immediately spread chocolate over grahams. Sprinkle with pecans; press lightly into chocolate. Cool completely. Break into 24 squares.